sentences: In 1929, she recorded at least four songs—including Lara's "Canalla" and "Mentira"—for the Victor label.
She was also an exclusive artist of radio station XEB in the 1930s.

sentences: María Valenta Pérez Escamilla (22 April 1903 – 18 March 1937), known professionally as Maruca Pérez, was a Mexican singer, known for being the first female performer of Agustín Lara's songs and one of the first Mexican tango singers.
